HEADWORD: Ablaqueate
<hw>Ab*la"que*ate</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>ablaqueatus</ets>, p. p. of. <ets>ablaqueare</ets>; fr.
<ets>ab</ets> + <ets>laqueus</ets> a noose.]</ety> <def>To lay bare, as
the roots of a tree.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
